# Security Protocols

## Secrets -- Never in Source Code

```kotlin
// ❌ BANNED -- hardcoded secrets
val supabaseKey = "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..."

// ✅ REQUIRED -- via BuildConfig from local.properties (gitignored)
val supabaseKey = BuildConfig.SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
```

All secrets live in `local.properties` (gitignored). Injected via `secrets-gradle-plugin` into `BuildConfig`.
`SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` must never appear in the Android app -- server/CI only.

## P2P Payload Encryption -- AES-256-GCM

All Protobuf packets must be encrypted before P2P transmission:

```kotlin
// Every payload leaving the device goes through SecurePayloadManager
val encrypted = securePayloadManager.encrypt(telemetry.toByteArray())
    .getOrElse { return Result.failure(it) }
nearbyClient.sendPayload(endpointId, Payload.fromBytes(encrypted))
```

- IV (12 bytes) prepended to ciphertext for each packet
- Key retrieved from Android Keystore, never from memory or shared prefs
- AES/GCM/NoPadding with 128-bit authentication tag

## Local Database -- SQLCipher

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD -- plaintext Room database
Room.databaseBuilder(context, SlickDatabase::class.java, "slick.db").build()

// ✅ REQUIRED -- SQLCipher encrypted
val passphrase = retrieveKeyFromKeystore()  // Android Keystore backed
val factory = SupportFactory(passphrase)
Room.databaseBuilder(context, SlickDatabase::class.java, "slick.db")
    .openHelperFactory(factory)
    .build()
```

## Android Keystore -- Key Management

```kotlin
// Key generation (one-time, on first launch)
val keyGen = KeyGenerator.getInstance(KeyProperties.KEY_ALGORITHM_AES, "AndroidKeyStore")
keyGen.init(
    KeyGenParameterSpec.Builder(ALIAS, KeyProperties.PURPOSE_ENCRYPT or KeyProperties.PURPOSE_DECRYPT)
        .setBlockModes(KeyProperties.BLOCK_MODE_GCM)
        .setEncryptionPaddings(KeyProperties.ENCRYPTION_PADDING_NONE)
        .setKeySize(256)
        .build()
)
keyGen.generateKey()
```

Key alias defined in `BuildConfig.SQLCIPHER_PASSPHRASE_ALIAS`.

## P2P Identity -- Rotating Ephemeral UUIDs

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD -- exposes real device identity
val advertisingName = Build.MODEL  // "Pixel 8"

// ✅ GOOD -- ephemeral, rotated per convoy session
val advertisingName = UUID.randomUUID().toString().take(8)  // e.g., "a3f9c201"
```

Real `riderId` (UUID) is only stored in the encrypted local Room database and the Supabase convoy session (with RLS).

## No PII in Logs

```kotlin
// ❌ BANNED
Timber.d("Rider at %.6f, %.6f".format(lat, lon))
Timber.d("User email: $email")

// ✅ ALLOWED -- UUIDs and operational data only
Timber.d("Node synced: %s", nodeId)
Timber.d("Breadcrumb cached, count=%d", pendingCount)
```

## Supabase Row Level Security

All tables require RLS. Convoy data must only be readable by verified convoy members:

```sql
-- Riders can only read their own breadcrumbs or convoy sessions they belong to
CREATE POLICY "convoy_member_access" ON rider_breadcrumbs
    FOR SELECT USING (
        auth.uid() = rider_id
        OR EXISTS (
            SELECT 1 FROM convoy_sessions
            WHERE convoy_sessions.id = rider_breadcrumbs.convoy_id
            AND auth.uid() = ANY(convoy_sessions.member_ids)
            AND convoy_sessions.ended_at > NOW() - INTERVAL '24 hours'
        )
    );
```

## Data Retention -- Purge on Finish

```kotlin
// After successful Supabase sync, purge local breadcrumbs
suspend fun flushAndPurge(): Result<Unit> {
    val flushed = supabaseClient.uploadBreadcrumbs(localBreadcrumbs).getOrElse { return Result.failure(it) }
    breadcrumbDao.clearAll()
    return Result.success(Unit)
}
```

Breadcrumbs not needed after sync. Route history deleted when ride is explicitly ended.

## CI Secret Scanner

GitHub Actions workflow must include a secret scanning step that blocks pushes containing API keys or JWT tokens. See `.github/workflows/android-build.yml`.
